ol"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Domestic Politics</CodeD><CodeI org="rbc" action="add"><CodeA name="rule" value="799599"/><CodeA name="db" value="prbc---00018569-20180321-145544"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="2"/></CodeI></Code><Code value="gcat"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Political/General News</CodeD><CodeI org="expansion" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="root" value="ns:gcrim"/><CodeA name="root" value="ns:gpol"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="0"/></CodeI></Code><Code value="gpir"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Politics/International Relations</CodeD><CodeI org="expansion" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="root" value="ns:gpol"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00000998-20180321-161406"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="1"/></CodeI></Code></CSet></CodeSets></MetadataPT><ArchiveDoc xml:space="preserve"><Article markup="pp0" lang="en" index="field"><HandL fid="hlp"><Title fid="hl"><SectionName fid="se" index="field">Top of the News</SectionName><ColumnName fid="clm" index="field"></ColumnName><Headline fid="hd"><Para lang="en">Why It Matters; Giving courts an objective picture</Para></Headline></Title><LeadPara fid="lp"><Para>Longstanding calls from criminal lawyers for police interviews with suspects to be recorded on video have finally been answered.</Para><Para>A legislative framework for the video recording of police interviews was approved by Parliament on Monday, along with wide-ranging changes to the Criminal Procedure Code.</Para></LeadPara></HandL><TailParas fid="td"><Para>The Code was last overhauled in 2010, when the Government had considered implementing video-recorded interviews, but decided against it.</Para><Para>Criminal lawyers continued to ask for it, saying a video would give the court an objective picture of what went on when a suspect gave a statement.</Para><Para>This would reduce the time spent on an accused person's challenge that his statement wasnot accurate or made voluntarily.</Para><Para>Currently, such statements are recorded in writing by the investigator. In revisiting the issue, the Government studied local conditions and best practices overseas before coming up with a model that would help the courts assess the voluntariness of a statement and the weight it should be given.</Para><Para>Given the significant investment in infrastructure and training, the video recording of interviews will be implemented in phases. The first phase will make video-recorded interviews mandatory for suspects in specified rape offences.</Para><Para>The procedures and training of police officers will be fine-tuned as the scheme is rolled out.</Para><Para>The move has been widely welcomed, although concerns have been raised, for instance, about the possibility that suspects could be put under duress off-camera.</Para><Para>Nagging questions notwithstanding, video-recorded interviews offer a safeguard to suspects from giving statements under duress, and deter frivolous allegations against investigators.</Para><Para>This saves the time that the court would otherwise have to spend on hearing additional testimony to decide whether a statement had been given voluntarily and, hence, is admissible in court.</Para></TailParas><Byline fid="by" index="field">Selina Lum </Byline><Credit fid="cr" index="field"></Credit><Contact fid="ct" index="field"></Contact><Notes fid="rf" index="field"></Notes><Art fid="art" index="field"></Art><Copyright fid="cy" index="field">(c) 2018 Singapore Press Holdings Limited </Copyright></Article></ArchiveDoc><AdocTOC adoctype="article"><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/ArchiveDoc::Article" type="arttext"></Item><Item size="0" ref="distdoc:archive/InvertText" type="invtext"></Item></AdocTOC></DistDoc>

